# Trim the build context. The Dockerfile COPY is selective (pyproject + README +
# LICENSE + vaxtract/), so the ONE hard rule is: never exclude anything the
# package needs. Directory excludes are ROOT-ANCHORED (leading /) so a bare name like
# `figure_benchmark` or `*.md` can't match INSIDE vaxtract/ at any depth and
# silently drop the figure subpackage / layer2_prompt_deltas.md (which is read at import).
.git
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
/tests
/outputs
/docs
/.docs
/lite_extract
/scale
/cancervac_packet
/build
/dist
/*.egg-info
/.venv*
# Not needed by the image and would bloat / break the context. `/data` is a
# symlink to the corpus outside this dir (a buildkit context-walk hazard);
# reference_records, the dev figures, and JS artifacts are dev-only.
/data
/reference_records
/node_modules
/package-lock.json
/package.json
/*.pdf
/*.png
